135 A.3d 452 ATTORNEY GRIEVANCE COMMISSION OF MARYLAND, Petitioner, v. Richard J. KWASNY, Respondent. Misc. Docket AG No. 89,

Sept. Term, 2015.

Court of Appeals of Maryland. April 25, 2016.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the Joint Petition for Disbarment by Consent filed herein pursuant to Maryland Rule 16-772, it is this 25th day of April, 2016,

ORDERED, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland, that Respondent, Richard J. Kwasny, be and he is hereby disbarred from the practice of law in the State of Maryland for violating Rules 1.15 and 8.4(c) of the Maryland Lawyers’ Rules of Professional Conduct; and it is further

ORDERED, that the Clerk of this Court shall remove the name of Richard J, Kwasny from the register of attorneys in the Court and certify that fact to the Trustees of the Client Protection Fund of the Bar of Maryland and all clerks of all judicial tribunals in this State in accordance with Maryland Rule 16-772(d).
